11.1 
  1) George was in bed.
  2) Carol and Jack were in a cinema.
  3) Sue was at the train station at 3 o'clock yesterday afternoon.
  4) Mr. and Mrs. Baker were at restaurant.
  5) Ben was at beach.
  6) I was at work yesterday afternoon.
  
11.2
  1) Last year she was 22, so she is 23 now.
  2) Today the weather is nice, buy yesterday it was cold.
  3) I'm hungry. Can I have something to eat?
  4) I was hungry last night, so I had something to eat.
  5) Where were you at 11 o'clock last Friday morning?
  6) Don't buy those shoes. They're too expensive.
  7) Why were you soo hungry yesterday?
  8) We must go now. It is very late.
  9) This time last year I was in Paris.
  10) We were tired when we arrived home, s we went to bed.
  11) Charlie Chaplin died in 1978. He was a famouse film star.
  12) Where are the children? I don't know. They were in the
      garden ten minutes ago.
      
11.3
  1) We didn't like our hotel room. It was very small and
    it wasn't very comfortable.
  2) Kate got married when she was 24 years old.
  3) I phoned you yesterday evening but you weren't at home.
     Where were you?
  4) Gearge wasn't at work last week because he was ill.
     He's better now.
  5) The shops weren't open yesterday because it was a pulic holiday.
  6) Were you at home at 9.30? No, I was at work.
  
11.4
  1) I saw a film. Was it good?
  2) I met some people. Were they friendly?
  3) I did an examination. Was it difficult?
  4) I bought some boots. Were they expensive?
  5) I went to a museum. Was it interesting?
  
  
  
